      <section class="faq-section">
        <div class="faq-container">
          <!-- Left Section (Heading and Description) -->
          <div class="faq-left">
            <h2 class="faq-heading">General FAQs</h2>
            <p class="faq-paragraph">Your guide to understanding how our jewelry works, the virtual try-on feature, and everything else you need to know to have the best shopping experience with us.</p>
          </div>
      
          <!-- Right Section (Collapsible Questions and Answers) -->
          <div class="faq-right">
            <div class="faq-item">
              <div class="faq-question">
                <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                <p class="faq-text">How do I use the virtual try-on feature?</p>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>To use the virtual try-on feature, simply click on any piece of jewelry and choose the "Try On" option. You'll be able to see how the piece looks on you using augmented reality technology.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
      
            <div class="faq-item">
              <div class="faq-question">
                <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                <p class="faq-text">Can I return a product after using the virtual try-on?</p>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Yes, you can return the jewelry within 30 days of receiving it, even if you have used the virtual try-on feature. Please refer to our return policy for more details.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
      
            <div class="faq-item">
              <div class="faq-question">
                <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                <p class="faq-text">Is the virtual try-on feature available on all jewelry?</p>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>Currently, the virtual try-on feature is available for most of our jewelry collection, excluding some items like rings that require specific measurements.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
      
            <div class="faq-item">
              <div class="faq-question">
                <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
                <p class="faq-text">What are the system requirements for virtual try-on?</p>
              </div>
              <div class="faq-answer">
                <p>You need a smartphone or tablet with a camera and AR support to use the virtual try-on feature. It works on both iOS and Android devices.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
      <section class="steps">
        <div class="steps-header">
          <h2>Steps to Try On</h2>
          <p>Follow these simple steps to try on our jewelry virtually and find the perfect match for you.</p>
        </div>
      
        <div class="steps-container">
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-icon">1</div>
            <div class="step-description">
              <h3>Step 1: Choose Your Jewelry</h3>
              <p>Browse through our stunning jewelry collection and choose the piece you'd like to try on.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
      
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-icon">2</div>
            <div class="step-description">
              <h3>Step 2: Enable Your Camera</h3>
              <p>Enable your camera to allow the virtual try-on feature to work seamlessly.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
      
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-icon">3</div>
            <div class="step-description">
              <h3>Step 3: Adjust the Jewelry</h3>
              <p>Adjust the size and position of the jewelry to see how it looks on you in real-time.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
      
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-icon">4</div>
            <div class="step-description">
              <h3>Step 4: Get Feedback</h3>
              <p>Get a clear view of how the jewelry looks on you and decide if it's the one!</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
